{
  "What is a recursive formula?": "",
  "A formula that defines each term based on the previous term(s)": "",
  "What is an explicit formula?": "",
  "A formula that calculates any term directly from its position number n": "",
  "Recursive for arithmetic:": "",
  "a(n) = a(n−1) + d, with a(1) given": "",
  "Recursive for geometric:": "",
  "a(n) = a(n−1) · r, with a(1) given": "",
  "Advantage of explicit formulas:": "",
  "You can find any term without computing all previous terms": "",
  "Write recursive formula for 2, 5, 8, 11, ...": "",
  "a(n) = a(n−1) + 3, a(1) = 2": "",
  "Write recursive formula for 4, 12, 36, ...": "",
  "a(n) = a(n−1) · 3, a(1) = 4": "",
  "Convert a(n) = a(n−1) + 5, a(1) = 3 to explicit:": "",
  "a(n) = 5n − 2": "",
  "Advantage of recursive formulas:": "",
  "Easy to compute the next term from the previous one": "",
  "Convert a(n) = a(n−1) · 2, a(1) = 5 to explicit:": "",
  "a(n) = 5 · 2^(n−1)": ""
